text: Gene Mitcham (May 18, 1932 – October 27, 2008) was an American football end. He played for the Philadelphia Eagles in 1958. He died on October 27, 2008, in Phoenix, Arizona at age 76. ==References== Category:1932 births Category:2008 deaths Category:American football ends Category:Arizona State Sun Devils football players Category:Philadelphia Eagles players
